WEBVTT

00:04.323 --> 00:05.456
JAMIE:
Hey.

00:05.458 --> 00:07.024
Russell.

00:07.026 --> 00:08.192
What do you got?

00:08.194 --> 00:09.326
Okay, there's been a series of
armed robberies

00:09.328 --> 00:10.561
in this neighborhood.

00:10.563 --> 00:13.063
And those two fit the
description to a tee.

00:13.065 --> 00:14.031
These guys?

00:14.033 --> 00:16.000
RUSSELL:
Yeah.

00:16.001 --> 00:17.535
Let's go.
Set?

00:17.537 --> 00:18.736
Yup.
Set.

00:24.544 --> 00:26.677
Hey, get your hands
out of your pockets!

00:26.679 --> 00:28.279
Go, go, go! Let's go!

00:28.281 --> 00:29.013
Hey! Police!

00:29.015 --> 00:30.781
JAMIE: Hey!
JANKO: Stop!

00:31.517 --> 00:32.448
(man grunts)

00:32.451 --> 00:33.918
JANKO:
Stop running!

00:34.954 --> 00:36.353
JAMIE:
Stop! Police!

00:36.355 --> 00:38.155
Watch it! Move it!
(people yelling, shouting)

00:38.758 --> 00:40.190
Aah!
Move it!

00:40.192 --> 00:42.726
Aah... (grunts)

00:44.063 --> 00:46.330
JAMIE:
Police!

00:51.671 --> 00:52.870
JAMIE:
Hands behind your back.

00:52.872 --> 00:54.104
Yeah.

00:54.106 --> 00:56.407
Stay in the car.
Stay in the car!

00:56.409 --> 00:57.775
Stop! Police!

00:57.777 --> 00:58.876
Stop!

00:58.878 --> 01:01.145
Oh, what do we have here?

01:01.147 --> 01:03.814
Huh. Okay.

01:03.816 --> 01:05.316
Look at this.

01:05.318 --> 01:06.483
Looks like you're going to jail.

01:06.485 --> 01:07.918
(distant gunshot)

01:09.655 --> 01:10.921
Call it in!

01:12.000 --> 01:18.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:22.101 --> 01:23.133
Russell!

01:23.135 --> 01:24.568
Russell, what happened?

01:24.570 --> 01:25.903
He refused to give up the knife.

01:25.905 --> 01:28.739
Th-Th-Then he started
coming toward me.

01:28.741 --> 01:29.940
Put your gun away.

01:29.942 --> 01:31.942
Hey, back up please.
Do me a favor, back up.

01:31.944 --> 01:33.143
WOMAN: You didn't even
give him a chance!

01:33.145 --> 01:35.479
(crowd clamoring)

01:35.481 --> 01:37.881
MAN:
You didn't have to shoot him!

01:37.883 --> 01:39.016
(crowd continues yelling)

01:39.018 --> 01:40.784
He had his hands up, man!

01:40.786 --> 01:42.519
You didn't have to shoot him!

01:43.623 --> 01:44.688
I had no choice.

01:44.690 --> 01:46.890
Hey, hey, look,
I swear to God, man.

01:46.892 --> 01:48.292
I had no choice.

01:48.294 --> 01:50.194
Don't say anything else, okay?

01:51.864 --> 01:53.297
(all yelling)

01:53.299 --> 01:54.298
Stop talking.

01:54.300 --> 01:55.666
(siren wailing)

01:55.668 --> 01:57.801
He's just a kid! A kid!

01:57.803 --> 01:59.770
MAN:
...he's dead!

01:59.772 --> 02:00.738
(clamor continues)

02:00.740 --> 02:02.239
Okay, everybody
please step back.

02:02.241 --> 02:03.507
Give us some room.

02:03.509 --> 02:05.042
Please step back.

02:08.481 --> 02:11.014
(panting, running footsteps
on body-camera video)

02:11.017 --> 02:12.016
RUSSELL: Hey!

02:12.018 --> 02:13.717
Hey, put that down!

02:13.719 --> 02:15.285
MAN: <i>No hice nada.</i>

02:15.287 --> 02:17.054
Put the- put the knife down!
<i>No hice nada!</i>

02:17.056 --> 02:19.823
<i>No hice nada.</i>
<i>No hice nada.</i>

02:19.825 --> 02:22.192
I said put it down!
<i>No hice nada.</i>

02:23.796 --> 02:25.696
(turns off video)

02:25.698 --> 02:27.431
How old was the kid?

02:27.433 --> 02:28.799
Seventeen.

02:28.801 --> 02:30.501
(inhales)
Seventeen.

02:30.503 --> 02:33.504
With items stolen
in an armed robbery

02:33.506 --> 02:35.973
that triggered the incident
on his person.

02:35.975 --> 02:38.142
So?

02:38.144 --> 02:39.543
That's now a capital offense?

02:39.545 --> 02:40.844
So, he's not just a kid,

02:40.846 --> 02:43.213
he's an armed felon
confronting one of my officers.

02:43.215 --> 02:44.715
Who brought a knife
to a gunfight.

02:44.717 --> 02:46.917
That's just a saying, Mr. Mayor.

02:46.919 --> 02:49.019
You're three times as likely
to die from a stabbing

02:49.021 --> 02:50.154
as you are a gunshot.

02:50.156 --> 02:52.690
Frank, what the hell
was your guy thinking,

02:52.692 --> 02:53.891
just blowing him away?

02:53.893 --> 02:56.493
He was thinking
what he was trained to think.

02:56.495 --> 02:59.163
The suspect repeatedly
ignored commands

02:59.165 --> 03:00.831
to throw down the weapon.

03:00.833 --> 03:01.832
His hands were in the air.

03:01.834 --> 03:02.933
And one of them held a knife.

03:02.935 --> 03:05.169
Look, there's no guarantee
a cop with a gun

03:05.171 --> 03:08.005
can stop a dedicated attacker
with a knife

03:08.007 --> 03:09.239
from twice that distance.

03:09.241 --> 03:10.274
That's not the point.

03:10.276 --> 03:11.608
It's exactly the point.

03:11.610 --> 03:13.277
He could've backed away.

03:13.279 --> 03:14.511
And let the perp flee
into the population,

03:14.513 --> 03:16.847
armed with a knife,
with nothing to lose?

03:16.849 --> 03:17.815
That's your advice?

03:17.817 --> 03:19.583
So, execution?

03:19.585 --> 03:21.285
That's the only other option?

03:23.789 --> 03:26.423
You really gonna
call this an execution?

03:27.693 --> 03:30.928
Maybe you need to think
about that for a second.

03:30.930 --> 03:33.931
And Frank, you really think
I'll be the only one?

03:33.933 --> 03:35.999
What do you think the people's
takeaway's gonna be here?

03:36.001 --> 03:37.034
Throw that cop a parade?

03:37.036 --> 03:39.236
Of course not,
but the fact remains,

03:39.238 --> 03:42.673
my officer reacted
as he was trained to.

03:42.675 --> 03:45.909
Listen, I didn't realize that
the Academy offered classes

03:45.911 --> 03:47.344
in killing teenagers.

03:47.346 --> 03:49.446
That's a cheap shot,
Mr. Mayor.

03:49.448 --> 03:50.681
Yes, it is,
to a bad shooting, Frank.

03:50.683 --> 03:51.682
Get used to them.

03:51.684 --> 03:53.217
You want to honor your office,

03:53.219 --> 03:55.452
help the public to understand.

03:55.454 --> 03:58.555
Frank, my office is the mayor.

03:58.557 --> 03:59.590
Of the people.

03:59.592 --> 04:02.159
Not PR for the NYPD.

04:02.161 --> 04:03.894
Execution?

04:03.896 --> 04:06.029
Listen, that's not my word.

04:06.031 --> 04:07.431
I will not say that.

04:07.433 --> 04:08.799
But I will make
a statement, Frank,

04:08.801 --> 04:10.000
and you're not gonna like it.

04:10.002 --> 04:11.668
Because it would be premature.

04:11.670 --> 04:13.704
No, Frank, because these
pictures tell a story

04:13.706 --> 04:14.872
that any fool could see.

04:14.874 --> 04:16.673
And I cannot wait
for the result--

04:16.675 --> 04:18.041
Oh, sure you can.

04:18.043 --> 04:20.209
Listen, I can't wait for the
results of an investigation

04:20.212 --> 04:22.112
not to express the outrage
that's happened here.

04:22.113 --> 04:24.615
By any measure of
responsibility,

04:24.617 --> 04:26.583
you should wait.

04:26.585 --> 04:28.719
But if you won't...

04:28.721 --> 04:31.989
please make damn sure
you do not condemn my officer

04:31.991 --> 04:34.324
for doing his job.

04:35.294 --> 04:37.761
And that is an order,
Commissioner?

04:39.565 --> 04:40.998
(sighs)

04:45.838 --> 04:49.838
